DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);
 
Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(3,11,2);

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find an antiderivative \(F(x)\) of 
\( f(x)=$a x - \sqrt{x} \).

$PAR
\(F(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(fun_cmp( "($a/2)*x^2 - (2/3)*x^(3/2)", 'mode'=>'antider' ) );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

We can write \(f(x) = $a x - x^{1/2}\), so \(F(x)\) must have the form 
\(F(x) = \frac{$a}{2} x^2 - \frac{2}{3} x^{3/2}\), or this plus any
constant value.

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


;
